Entries.default: The air around you thickens with a choking miasma. You clutch at your throat to draw breath, but relief never comes. Up ahead, a familiar shape grows in definition - the silhouette of the Pallid Knight.

She shakes her head and reaches a pale hand into your chest. Waves of disapproval, tinged with a feeling of unfinished business, fill you with cold dread. 

There was something she wanted. A crucial errand. What was it?

You die repeating the question to yourself in a panicked loop. Then you stop. As your soul drifts away from your body, answers don't seem to matter anymore. Nothing does. Letting go is both easier and simpler than you imagined.
